<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>For You Baby 💜</title>

<style>

body{
font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
background: linear-gradient(135deg,#8e44ad,#c39bd3);
text-align:center;
padding-top:100px;
color:white;
}

.container{
background:white;
color:#5b2c6f;
width:80%;
max-width:500px;
margin:auto;
padding:30px;
border-radius:20px;
box-shadow:0 10px 25px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
}

button{
padding:12px 25px;
margin:10px;
border:none;
border-radius:20px;
font-size:16px;
cursor:pointer;
}

.yes{
background:#8e44ad;
color:white;
}

.no{
background:#bbb;
color:white;
}

#message{
display:none;
margin-top:20px;
line-height:1.6;
}

img{
width:200px;
border-radius:15px;
margin-top:15px;
}

</style>

</head>

<body>

<div class="container">

<h2>Hi Baby 💜</h2>
<p>I made something for you...</p>

<p>Do you want to open your birthday message? 🎁</p>

<button class="yes" onclick="showMessage()">Yes 💜</button>
<button class="no" onclick="noMessage()">No 🙈</button>

<div id="message">

<img src="photo.jpg">

<p>
Happy 19th Birthday, baby. I don’t know what to say but I just want to remind u that i’m so grateful that i have u wab, and as you 19 today, i hope it brings you happiness, more blessings and success baby. I hope you achieve all your dreams in your life (with me). Remember that no matter what happens, i will always be here for you baby. Enjoy your day baby. Happy 19th birthday again, baby. Iloveyousomuch.
</p>

</div>

</div>

<script>

function showMessage(){
document.getElementById("message").style.display="block";
}

function noMessage(){
alert("Aww baby 😭 please press YES 💜");
}

</script>

</body>
</html>
